1) switching off the pc while performing the task on remote computer
	Use screen commands
	https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/9660/how-can-i-keep-processes-running-on-a-remote-server-even-after-turning-off-the-t
2) wget 
	wget -r -nc -U  -U "Opera 11.0" https://www.cs.toronto.edu/~vmnih/data/
	-r = recursive
	-nc = no copy 
	-U "Opera 11.0" for behaving like opera browser ( as some sites may not allow some data to be scrapped by wget )
3) running a command on startup of Ubuntu
	https://stackoverflow.com/questions/8339555/how-to-run-a-script-at-the-start-up-of-ubuntu
	sudo vim /etc/rc.local

